data.title: List of All DTH Channel Number with Price
data.meta_description: Choose your favorite HD and SD channels for the list of all Airtel DTH channel number with price and validity. Unlock the world of entertainment with Airtel Digital TV channels.
data.text:
You will get a total of 40 channels with the Bengali Basic HD 1 Month Pack from Airtel DTH. Thus, for a tiny amount of ₹209, you can now watch DTH channels across multiple genres, ranging from movies, music, news, sports, regional languages, and lots more. All of this ensures that you are really getting the best value-for-money deal from this Bengali Basic HD 1 Month plan.

With Airtel DTH, you will get to choose from over 550 channels. As a user of Airtel digital TV, you can select from a wide variety of channels, ranging from movies, soap operas, documentaries, news, and music. Broadly put, you can go for two kinds of channel packs, namely Broadcaster pack and Ala Carte. While the former subscription plan will grant you access to all the channels offered by a particular broadcaster, an Ala Carte pack will let you pick and choose individual channels as per your own liking.

You can add a channel to your existing list of the same on your Airtel DTH in several convenient ways. You can either do the same through the Airtel Thanks app or the official website of Airtel. You will simply need to log in with your credentials and follow the simple laid-out procedure. Alternatively, you can just text ADD (Channel Number) to 54325 from your registered mobile number.

You can remove a channel from your list of the same easily in several ways. You can either do it through the Airtel Thanks app or Airtel’s official website. All you must do is log in with your ID and password and then follow the simple procedure.

Alternatively, you can just text REM (Channel number) to 54325 from your registered mobile number. Kindly keep in mind that you will need to keep your set-top box on while doing so. You can also remove the channels in the middle of the month, but you will be charged the Ala carte price for that channel, depending on your connection type.

Airtel DTH offers over 500 channels and services, including a mix of regional, national, and international channels. The service provides features like an electronic program guide (EPG), interactive channels, pay-per-view movies, and parental control. There are two types of set-top boxes that can be used to watch Airtel DTH content.

They are as follows:

. Airtel HD/SD set-top box

. Airtel Xstream Box

Both set-top boxes support all channels available with Airtel Digital TV (SD set-top box can’t support HD channels).

Types of Airtel DTH Channels List

Airtel DTH offers a wide range of channels across different languages and genres. The channels available may vary based on the specific plan or package selected by the customer. Here is a general overview of the channels available on Airtel DTH:

Entertainment Channels: Star Plus, Zee TV, Sony TV, Colors, &TV, SAB TV, Sony Sab HD, Star Plus HD, Zee TV HD, Colors HD, &TV HD, and more.

Movie Channels: Zee Cinema, Sony Max, Star Gold, &pictures, UTV Movies, B4U Movies, Zee Cinema HD, Star Gold HD, Sony Max HD, and more.

Sports Channels: Star Sports 1, Star Sports 2, Sony Ten 1, Sony Ten 2, Sony Ten 3, Star Sports HD 1, Star Sports HD 2, Sony Ten 1 HD, Sony Ten 2 HD, Sony Ten 3 HD, and more.

News Channels: Aaj Tak, ABP News, NDTV India, Zee News, India TV, News18 India, DD News, India Today, Republic TV, Times Now, NDTV 24x7, CNN-News18, and more.

Kids Channels: Cartoon Network, Pogo, Disney Channel, Disney Junior, Hungama TV, Nick, Sonic, and more.

Music Channels: MTV, Sony Mix, B4U Music, 9XM, VH1, Mastiii, and more.

Lifestyle Channels: Discovery, TLC, NDTV Good Times, Living Foodz, and more.

Regional Channels: Sun TV, Gemini TV, Colors Tamil, Star Maa, Zee Marathi, Colors Kannada, and more.

You can refer to the complete list on this page for more details. Choose your favorite channels from the list and recharge your Airtel DTH account with the same. If you can’t find all your favorite channels in one single pack, add that channel by using the a-la-carte method! It’s that simple with Airtel.

Once you have chosen the pack, recharge your account from the comfort of your home.

Ways to Recharge Airtel DTH Channels

There are multiple ways to recharge your Airtel DTH account.

Online Recharge: You can recharge your Airtel DTH account online through the Airtel Thanks app or the Airtel DTH website. Simply log in to your account, select the recharge option, and choose your preferred payment method.

Airtel Payments Bank: If you have an Airtel Payments Bank account, you can use it to recharge your Airtel DTH account.

Airtel DTH Retailers: You can visit an Airtel DTH retailer near you to recharge your account. Provide your customer ID to the retailer and make the payment.
